The Telegraph - Calcutta : Sport
		 Friday, July 16, 2004  IN THE CITY
				 																																																	 Bengals most successful spinner in domestic cricket, Utpal Chatterjee has been named the specialised spinners coach for the state teams in all age groups, including the senior outfit. Utpal, who announced his retirement from first-class cricket recently, will be attending the camps for each group once a week as part of his new assignment from next week. 				 																																																	Meanwhile, former Bengal and Mohun Bagan captain P.B. Dutta has been chosen as the first recipient of the CABs lifetime achievement award. The award has been named after Kartik Bose and contains Rs 1 lakh and a memento. Dutta, it has been learnt, pipped Premanshu Chatterjee as the two were shortlisted from a pack of former Bengal greats like Shibaji Bose, Prakash Poddar, Arun Lal and Ashok Malhotra during a CAB meeting on Thursday. Dutta, a Cambridge University Blue, played for Bengal from 1947-48 to 1957-58. Later, he was attached with the CAB in various capacities. 				 																																																	FOOTBALL: CFL Super Division  CFC vs Mod. AC (Mohun Bagan); FCI vs RFC (BNMC); Peerless SC vs Eastern Railway (Howrah Stadium). 1st division group B  Spo. Union vs Barisha SC (R. Sarobar); Janbazar vs Taltala Inst. (Md. Sp); Behala Youth vs Bata (Juger Protik); Jessop Anushilani vs United Student (Tarun Sangha); Garalgacha SC vs Kalighat MS (SAP-II); Rajasthan vs Salkia Fds (E. Bengal). Matches from 3.30 pm. 				 																																																	SWIMMING: All Bengal meet at CSA course (Rabindra Sarobar)  Opening day action from 3.30 pm.
